status_notes: Case Noted. Thank you for contacting the Boston Transportation Department. Painting individual spaces not only has maintenance and budget impacts, but it actually reduces the number of available spaces overall. This is because the spaces would need to be marked to fit all vehicles. A car is approx. 14-16ft long, however, the federal standard for marked spaces is 22ft long. This would leave about a 6ft gap between each and every car (instead of the few that park like this currently). Natural (unmarked) parking yields more spaces and allows vehicles of all lengths to park more efficiently.
